        <initializer>= 0</initializer>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>FastScan k-NN only: maximum number of inverted lists to visit. 0 means unlimited, i.e. bounded only by nprobe. When set together with max_codes, either budget may stop the scan. With ensure_topk_full, this limit is treated as at least k lists. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
